President Obama issued a statement wishing everyone celebrating Passover a happy holiday. He mentioned that he and his family will be holding a Seder in the White House for the seventh year in a row. He highlighted the significance of the Exodus story and how it has inspired generations throughout history. He emphasized the importance of faith, courage, and hope in times of struggle. The President also mentioned the need to continue working towards a more perfect union and extending freedom and peace to more people around the world. He concluded by expressing his desire for a happy Passover to all.